contentrichtext.text: {{Wiktionary|eno}} '''Eno''' may refer to: {{TOC right}} == Music == * [[English National Opera]], located at the Coliseum Theatre in St. Martin's Lane * ''Eno'', an album by Japanese band [[Polysics]] * "Eno", a song by X-Wife from ''[[Rockin' Rio EP]]'' == Places == * [[Eno, Finland]], a former municipality, now part of Joensuu * [[Eno, North Carolina]], a settlement * [[Eno River]], in North Carolina == People == * [[Eno people]], American Indian tribe * [[Amos Eno]] (1810-1898), owner of the Fifth Avenue Hotel, New York * [[Brian Eno]] (born 1948), English electronic musician, music theorist and record producer * [[Daikan Enō]], the Japanese name of Zen patriarch Dajian Huineng * [[Henry Lane Eno]] (1871–1928), American banker, poet and philanthropist * [[Jim Eno]] (born 1966), one of the founding members of the band Spoon * [[Kenji Eno]] (born 1970), Japanese musician and video game designer * [[Roger Eno]] (born 1959), English ambient composer, brother of Brian * [[William Phelps Eno]] (1858–1945), American businessman * [[Eno Raud]] (1928–1996), Estonian children's books writer == Other == * [[European Northern Observatory]], a group of astronomical observatories * [[Eno (drug)]], an over the counter medication produced by GlaxoSmithKline * [[En'ō]], a Japanese era after Ryakunin and before Ninji * [[Exhaled nitric oxide]], a breath test most commonly used in asthma * [[Environment Online]], an international educational network related to the environment and sustainable development {{disambiguation}}
